==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Corrival
<hw>Cor*ri"val</hw> <pr>(k?r-r?"v<it>a</it>l)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>A
fellow rival; a competitor; a rival; also, a companion.</def>
<mark>[R.]</mark> <rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Corrival</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Corrival
<hw>Cor*ri"val</hw>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Having rivaling claims; emulous;
in rivalry.</def> <mark>[R.]</mark> <rj><au>Bp. Fleetwood.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Corrival</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 3 ====
HEADWORD: Corrival
<hw>Cor*ri"val</hw>, <pos>v. i. & t.</pos> <def>To compete with; to
rival.</def> <mark>[R.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Corrivalry</ent>⟦br⟧
